{"lemma":"جان","slug":"جان","root":"NTWS","root_slug":"NTWS","root_link":"/words/roots/NTWS","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"جان","root":"جنن","pos":"N","occurrence_count":7},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n6397","n6508","n6769"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AC%D8%A7%D9%86"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"guilty, delinquent, criminal, flagrant, vicious, evil"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"gatherer, harvester, harvestman, reaper"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"perpetrator, offender, delinquent, criminal, culprit, felon, evildoer"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"snake, serpent"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Jānn, the forefather of the race of jinn","tags":["proper-noun"],"examples":[{"text":"وقد كان فيها قبل أن يخلق بألفي عام الجن بنو الجان، ففسدوا في الأرض.","english":"Two thousand years before [Adam] He [God] created the jinn, the sons of Jann, on earth, and they spread corruption and shed blood therein."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a jinn; a genie, a jann.","tags":["Classical","rare"],"examples":[{"text":"لَمْ يَطْمِثْهُنَّ إِنْسٌ قَبْلَهُمْ وَلَا جَانٌّ","english":"touched them has not mankind before them nor a jinn."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a serpentine or draconic class of the jinn"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"any supernatural being in general, especially elves and fairies.","tags":["in-plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of جَنَى (janā, “to gather, to harvest; to commit a crime”).\n\nHas the form derived from the active participle, as if from جَنَّ (janna, “to hide”) (in the passive جُنَّ (junna, “to go crazy”))."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n6397","headword_ar":"جَانٌّ","root":"jn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": se